people.careerHistory:
2004-2007 - worked in the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Kazakhstan: attache, third secretary of the State Protocol Service, third secretary of the Department of Europe and Africa, third, second secretary of the Registrar Office of the Ministry;
2007 -2011 - worked in the office of the Senate of the Parliament of the Republic of Kazakhstan: chief expert of the secretariat of the Chairman of the Senate, chief consultant, head of sector of interparliamentary relations and international cooperation unit, deputy head, head of unit for interaction with the International Relations, Defense and Security Committee;
2011-2012 - Head of South Asia and the Middle East division of the Asia and Africa Department of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Kazakhstan;
2012-2017 - Advisor to the Embassy of the Republic of Kazakhstan in France, Advisor to the Administration and Control Department of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Kazakhstan;
2017-2019 - Advisor to the Chairman of the Senate of the Parliament of the Republic of Kazakhstan, head of unit for interaction with the International Relations, Defense and Security Committee, Advisor to the Chairman of the Senate;
May 2019 to September 2019 - Ambassador on special assignment of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Kazakhstan;
September 2019 to July 2021 - Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the Republic of Kazakhstan to the Republic of Serbia;
July 2021 to February 2023 - First Deputy Head of Registrar Office of the Prime Minister of Kazakhstan;
February 2023 to September 2023. - First Deputy Chief of Staff of the Government of the Republic of Kazakhstan;
September 5, 2023 to the present, mayor of Shymkent city.

